HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 525
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Robin McCord on her
selection as the 2024–2025 Cannon County
School District Grades PreK-4 Teacher of the
Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Robin McCord is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. McCord has been selected as the 2024–2025 Cannon County School
District Grades PreK-4 Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive
influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Robin McCord is a PreK teacher at Cannon County Elementary School, in
which position she has served for fifteen years; in addition to her work in the classroom, she has
participated in many leadership and community involvement projects, such as helping with
outreach services for families in crisis, acting as a VPK PreK teacher for multiple years, being a
community PreK advisory teacher representative, and serving as a Tennessee Promise mentor;
and
WHEREAS, steeping herself in further study to better her teaching, Mrs. McCord
graduated from Tennessee Technological University with a Bachelor of Arts degree in
Elementary Education and subsequently earned her Master of Arts degree in Educational
Leadership from Austin Peay State University, from which she graduated with honors; and
